            "question": "Which muscle group plays a primary role in stabilizing a proximal joint segment during distal active movement?",
            "options": [
                "Agonists",
                "Antagonists",
                "Fixators (Stabilizers)",
                "Synergists"
            ],
            "answer": "Fixators (Stabilizers)",
            "explanation": "Fixators (Stabilizers) contract statically to steady the proximally located bone segments, providing a stable foundation for distal movement."
